<br>
There should only be 4 or 5 flags total, one for each &quot;tier&quot; of zones, and several different encounters that reward players with each flag. Lower level flags are a prerequisite for obtaining the next one up. Fewer unique flags and more parallel paths for getting them means that guilds with a mix of hardcore and less hardcore members can stay together. <br>
<br>
But, there's no chance of anything like good old common sense taking hold here. Verant made the same mistake with the old Plane of Sky (5 million unique quest components for 50 rewards, so noone goes there) and with Dozekar quests (2 million quest components for 20 rewards, so 95% of guilds ended up on giant faction).  <p>&lt;CENTER&gt;<br>
